        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(diagnostics): keep local model calls running",
        "body": "Fixes #85826.\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nLocal and self-hosted model calls could be killed by the diagnostic stalled-session active-abort path even though they are expected to run for a long time.\r\nThis change carries the same local-provider fact used by the LLM idle timeout code into diagnostic model-call events.\r\nDiagnostics still log stalled local model calls, but they no longer actively abort them.\r\nRemote and cloud model calls keep the diagnostic active-abort recovery behavior.\r\n\r\n## What Changed\r\n\r\nThe diagnostic event path now knows whether a model call should allow active abort recovery.\r\nLocal loopback, private-network, and `.local` providers are treated the same way as the idle timeout logic already treats them.\r\nOllama `*:cloud` models routed through local Ollama still count as cloud and remain abortable.\r\n\r\n- Added `allowActiveAbort` to prepared model-call diagnostic events.\r\n- Reused the local-model classification from the LLM idle timeout path.\r\n- Preserved stalled-session diagnostic logging for local model calls.\r\n- Skipped active abort recovery only for local model calls.\r\n- Added regression coverage for local/self-hosted and cloud-routed behavior.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\nThe targeted diagnostics and model-call timeout tests were run for the touched behavior.\r\nFormatting, lint, diff checks, and local autoreview were also run before opening this PR.\r\n\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts`\r\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.ts src/logging/diagnostic-run-activity.ts src/logging/diagnostic.ts src/infra/diagnostic-events.ts src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts`\r\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.ts src/logging/diagnostic-run-activity.ts src/logging/diagnostic.ts src/infra/diagnostic-events.ts src/logging/diagnostic.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/llm-idle-timeout.test.ts src/agents/pi-embedded-runner/run/attempt.model-diagnostic-events.test.ts`\r\n- `git diff --check`\r\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\nBehavior addressed: Local/self-hosted model calls should not be killed by diagnostic active-abort recovery when the provider is loopback, private-network, or `.local`. Remote/cloud model calls should still remain abortable, including Ollama `*:cloud` models routed through local Ollama.\r\n\r\nReal environment tested: The original failure was reproduced with a long local LM Studio/vLLM-style model call using diagnostics configured with `stuckSessionWarnMs=2000` and `stuckSessionAbortMs=6000`.\r\n\r\nExact steps or command run after this patch: The targeted unit/regression commands listed in the Testing section were run after the patch.\r\n\r\nEvidence after fix: Regression tests now assert that local model diagnostic events set `allowActiveAbort: false`, while cloud model calls keep `allowActiveAbort: true`.\r\n\r\nObserved result after fix: Diagnostics can still classify and log stalled local model calls, but the active-abort recovery path is skipped for those local calls.\r\n\r\nWhat was not tested: The full long-running LM Studio/vLLM live repro was not rerun after the patch.\r\n\r\n## Risks\r\n\r\nThe main risk is misclassifying a provider as local or cloud.\r\nThe change uses the existing idle-timeout classification so diagnostic active-abort behavior matches the already-shipped timeout behavior.\r\nCloud-routed Ollama models are explicitly covered so they do not lose active-abort recovery.\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/local-model-diagnostic-abort",
